fields.title: Psycho
fields.synopsis: A Phoenix secretary embezzles $40,000 from her employer's client, goes on the run, and checks into a remote motel run by a young man under the domination of his mother.

fields.title: Baby Driver
fields.synopsis: After being coerced into working for a crime boss, a young getaway driver finds himself taking part in a heist doomed to fail.

fields.title: School of Rock
fields.synopsis: After being kicked out of his rock band, Dewey Finn becomes a substitute teacher of an uptight elementary private school, only to try and turn his class into a rock band.

fields.title: Coco
fields.synopsis: Aspiring musician Miguel, confronted with his family's ancestral ban on music, enters the Land of the Dead to find his great-great-grandfather, a legendary singer.

fields.title: Manchester by the Sea
fields.synopsis: A depressed uncle is asked to take care of his teenage nephew after the boy's father dies.

fields.title: La La Land
fields.synopsis: While navigating their careers in Los Angeles, a pianist and an actress fall in love while attempting to reconcile their aspirations for the future.

fields.title: No Time To Die
fields.synopsis: James Bond has left active service. His peace is short-lived when Felix Leiter, an old friend from the CIA, turns up asking for help, leading Bond onto the trail of a mysterious villain armed with dangerous new technology.

fields.title: Carol
fields.synopsis: An aspiring photographer develops an intimate relationship with an older woman in 1950s New York.

fields.title: Arrival
fields.synopsis: A linguist works with the military to communicate with alien lifeforms after twelve mysterious spacecraft appear around the world.

fields.title: The Fugitive
fields.synopsis: Dr. Richard Kimble, unjustly accused of murdering his wife, must find the real killer while being the target of a nationwide manhunt led by a seasoned U.S. Marshal.

fields.title: The Bridge on the River Kwai
fields.synopsis: British POWs are forced to build a railway bridge across the river Kwai for their Japanese captors in occupied Burma, not knowing that the allied forces are planning a daring commando raid through the jungle to destroy it.

fields.title: The Good the Bad and the Ugly
fields.synopsis: A bounty hunting scam joins two men in an uneasy alliance against a third in a race to find a fortune in gold buried in a remote cemetery.

fields.title: Rush
fields.synopsis: The merciless 1970s rivalry between Formula One rivals James Hunt and Niki Lauda.

fields.title: The Lord of the Rings: The Return of the King
fields.synopsis: Gandalf and Aragorn lead the World of Men against Sauron's army to draw his gaze from Frodo and Sam as they approach Mount Doom with the One Ring.

fields.title: Dear Zachary: A Letter to a Son About His Father
fields.synopsis: A filmmaker decides to memorialize a murdered friend when his friend's ex-girlfriend announces she is expecting his son.

fields.title: Game of Thrones - Complete Series
fields.synopsis: Nine noble families fight for control over the lands of Westeros, while an ancient enemy returns after being dormant for millennia.

fields.title: Free Solo
fields.synopsis: Alex Honnold attempts to become the first person to ever free solo climb El Capitan.

fields.title: My Octopus teacher
fields.synopsis: A filmmaker forges an unusual friendship with an octopus living in a South African kelp forest, learning as the animal shares the mysteries of her world.

fields.title: Inside Job
fields.synopsis: Takes a closer look at what brought about the 2008 financial meltdown.

fields.title: Senna
fields.synopsis: A documentary on Brazilian Formula One racing driver Ayrton Senna, who won the F1 world championship three times before his death at age 34.

fields.title: Abducted in Plain Sight
fields.synopsis: The twisting, turning, stranger-than-fiction true story of the Brobergs, a naive, church-going Idaho family that fell under the spell of a sociopathic neighbor with designs on their twelve-year-old daughter.

fields.title: Blackfish
fields.synopsis: A documentary following the controversial captivity of killer whales, and its dangers for both humans and whales.

fields.title: The Act of Killing
fields.synopsis: A documentary which challenges former Indonesian death-squad leaders to reenact their mass-killings in whichever cinematic genres they wish, including classic Hollywood crime scenarios and lavish musical numbers.

fields.title: Amy
fields.synopsis: Archival footage and personal testimonials present an intimate portrait of the life and career of British singer/songwriter Amy Winehouse.

fields.title: Man on Wire
fields.synopsis: A look at tightrope walker Philippe Petit's daring, but illegal, high-wire routine performed between New York City's World Trade Center's twin towers in 1974, what some consider, "the artistic crime of the century".

fields.title: Voyage of Time: Life's Journey
fields.synopsis: An exploration into our planetary past and a search for humanity's place in the future. With narration by Cate Blanchett.

fields.title: Minding The Gap
fields.synopsis: Three young men bond together to escape volatile families in their Rust-Belt hometown. As they face adult responsibilities, unexpected revelations threaten their decade-long friendship.

fields.title: Love, Death & Robots - Season 1
fields.synopsis: A collection of animated short stories that span various genres including science fiction, fantasy, horror and comedy.

fields.title: Squid Game
fields.synopsis: Hundreds of cash-strapped players accept a strange invitation to compete in children's games. Inside, a tempting prize awaits with deadly high stakes. A survival game that has a whopping 45.6 billion-won prize at stake.

fields.title: Sweet Home
fields.synopsis: Hyun, a loner high school student who lost his entire family in a terrible accident, is forced to leave his home and has to face a new reality where monsters are trying to wipe out all of humanity. Now he must fight against all odds to try and race against the clock to save what is left of the human race before it's too late.

fields.title: Alice in Borderland
fields.synopsis: A group of bored delinquents are transported to a parallel dimension as part of a survival game.

fields.title: Attack on Titan: Seasons 1-3
fields.synopsis: After his hometown is destroyed and his mother is killed, young Eren Jaeger vows to cleanse the earth of the giant humanoid Titans that have brought humanity to the brink of extinction.

fields.title: The Office
fields.synopsis: The story of an office that faces closure when the company decides to downsize its branches. A documentary film crew follow staff and the manager David Brent as they continue their daily lives.

fields.title: Tales From The Loop
fields.synopsis: The townspeople who live above "The Loop," a machine built to unlock and explore the mysteries of the universe, experience things previously consigned to the realm of science fiction.

fields.title: Devs
fields.synopsis: A computer engineer investigates the secretive development division in her company, which she believes is behind the disappearance of her boyfriend.

fields.title: Who Is America
fields.synopsis: Sacha Baron Cohen offers his take on America's patriotism.

fields.title: Black Mirror Complete Series
fields.synopsis: An anthology series exploring a twisted, high-tech multiverse where humanity's greatest innovations and darkest instincts collide.

fields.title: Modern Family - Complete Series
fields.synopsis: Three different but related families face trials and tribulations in their own uniquely comedic ways.

fields.title: Your Honor
fields.synopsis: A judge confronts his convictions when his son is involved in a hit-and-run that embroils an organized-crime family. Facing impossible choices, he discovers how far a father will go to save his son's life.

fields.title: Death Note
fields.synopsis: An intelligent high school student goes on a secret crusade to eliminate criminals from the world after discovering a notebook capable of killing anyone whose name is written into it.

fields.title: Drive to Survive - Season 1
fields.synopsis: Docuseries following the FIA Formula One World Championship across multiple seasons.

fields.title: Sex Education Complete Series
fields.synopsis: A teenage boy with a sex therapist mother teams up with a high school classmate to set up an underground sex therapy clinic at school.

fields.title: Interstellar
fields.synopsis: A team of explorers travel through a wormhole in space in an attempt to ensure humanity's survival.

fields.title: Spirited Away
fields.synopsis: During her family's move to the suburbs, a sullen 10-year-old girl wanders into a world ruled by gods, witches, and spirits, and where humans are changed into beasts.

fields.title: Les Misérables
fields.synopsis: In 19th-century France, Jean Valjean, who for decades has been hunted by the ruthless policeman Javert after breaking parole, agrees to care for a factory worker's daughter. The decision changes their lives forever.

fields.title: Her
fields.synopsis: In a near future, a lonely writer develops an unlikely relationship with an operating system designed to meet his every need.

April 6th, 1917. As an infantry battalion assembles to wage war deep in enemy territory, two soldiers are assigned to race against time and deliver a message that will stop 1,600 men from walking straight into a deadly trap.

fields.title: The Hateful Eight
fields.synopsis: In the dead of a Wyoming winter, a bounty hunter and his prisoner find shelter in a cabin currently inhabited by a collection of nefarious characters.

fields.title: Ford V Ferrari
fields.synopsis: American car designer Carroll Shelby and driver Ken Miles battle corporate interference and the laws of physics to build a revolutionary race car for Ford in order to defeat Ferrari at the 24 Hours of Le Mans in 1966.

fields.title: The Lord of the Rings: The Fellowship of the Ring
fields.synopsis: A meek Hobbit from the Shire and eight companions set out on a journey to destroy the powerful One Ring and save Middle-earth from the Dark Lord Sauron.

fields.title: The Lord of the Rings: The Two Towers
fields.synopsis: While Frodo and Sam edge closer to Mordor with the help of the shifty Gollum, the divided fellowship makes a stand against Sauron's new ally, Saruman, and his hordes of Isengard.

fields.title: Mad Max: Fury Road
fields.synopsis: In a post-apocalyptic wasteland, a woman rebels against a tyrannical ruler in search for her homeland with the aid of a group of female prisoners, a psychotic worshiper, and a drifter named Max.

fields.title: Superbad
fields.synopsis: Two co-dependent high school seniors are forced to deal with separation anxiety after their plan to stage a booze-soaked party goes awry.

fields.title: Soul
fields.synopsis: After landing the gig of a lifetime, a New York jazz pianist suddenly finds himself trapped in a strange land between Earth and the afterlife.

fields.title: Roma
fields.synopsis: A year in the life of a middle-class family's maid in Mexico City in the early 1970s.

fields.title: Don't Breathe
fields.synopsis: Hoping to walk away with a massive fortune, a trio of thieves break into the house of a blind man who isn't as helpless as he seems.

fields.title: Mamma Mia!
fields.synopsis: The story of a bride-to-be trying to find her real father told using hit songs by the popular 1970s group ABBA.

fields.title: A Star is Born
fields.synopsis: A musician helps a young singer find fame as age and alcoholism send his own career into a downward spiral.

fields.title: Ex Machina
fields.synopsis: A young programmer is selected to participate in a ground-breaking experiment in synthetic intelligence by evaluating the human qualities of a highly advanced humanoid A.I.

fields.title: The Dark Knight
fields.synopsis: When the menace known as the Joker wreaks havoc and chaos on the people of Gotham, Batman must accept one of the greatest psychological and physical tests of his ability to fight injustice.

fields.title: Hacksaw ridge
fields.synopsis: World War II American Army Medic Desmond T. Doss, who served during the Battle of Okinawa, refuses to kill people and becomes the first man in American history to receive the Medal of Honor without firing a shot.

fields.title: Django Uncahined
fields.synopsis: With the help of a German bounty-hunter, a freed slave sets out to rescue his wife from a brutal plantation-owner in Mississippi.

fields.title: Warrior
fields.synopsis: The youngest son of an alcoholic former boxer returns home, where he's trained by his father for competition in a mixed martial arts tournament - a path that puts the fighter on a collision course with his estranged, older brother.

fields.title: Thor Ragnarok
fields.synopsis: Imprisoned on the planet Sakaar, Thor must race against time to return to Asgard and stop Ragnarök, the destruction of his world, at the hands of the powerful and ruthless villain Hela.

fields.title: Top Gun Maverick
fields.synopsis: After more than thirty years of service as one of the Navy's top aviators, Pete Mitchell is where he belongs, pushing the envelope as a courageous test pilot and dodging the advancement in rank that would ground him.

fields.title: Trainwreck
fields.synopsis: Having thought that monogamy was never possible, a commitment-phobic career woman may have to face her fears when she meets a good guy.

fields.title: Encanto
fields.director: Jared Bush, Byron Howard and Charise Castro Smith
fields.synopsis: A Colombian teenage girl has to face the frustration of being the only member of her family without magical powers.

fields.title: Parasite
fields.synopsis: Greed and class discrimination threaten the newly formed symbiotic relationship between the wealthy Park family and the destitute Kim clan.

fields.title: Midsommar
fields.synopsis: A couple travels to Northern Europe to visit a rural hometown's fabled Swedish mid-summer festival. What begins as an idyllic retreat quickly devolves into an increasingly violent and bizarre competition at the hands of a pagan cult.

fields.title: Mamma Mia! Here We Go Again
fields.synopsis: Five years after the events of Mamma Mia! (2008), Sophie prepares for the grand reopening of the Hotel Bella Donna as she learns more about her mother's past.

fields.title: Marriage Story
fields.synopsis: Noah Baumbach's incisive and compassionate look at a marriage breaking up and a family staying together.

fields.title: Blade Runner 2049
fields.synopsis: Young Blade Runner K's discovery of a long-buried secret leads him to track down former Blade Runner Rick Deckard, who's been missing for thirty years.

fields.title: Joker
fields.synopsis: A mentally troubled stand-up comedian embarks on a downward spiral that leads to the creation of an iconic villain.

fields.title: Inglorious Basterds
fields.synopsis: In Nazi-occupied France during World War II, a plan to assassinate Nazi leaders by a group of Jewish U.S. soldiers coincides with a theatre owner's vengeful plans for the same.

fields.title: Wind River
fields.synopsis: A veteran hunter helps an FBI agent investigate the murder of a young woman on a Wyoming Native American reservation.

fields.title: Creed
fields.synopsis: The former World Heavyweight Champion Rocky Balboa serves as a trainer and mentor to Adonis Johnson, the son of his late friend and former rival Apollo Creed.

fields.title: Tomb Raider
fields.synopsis: Lara Croft (Alicia Vikander), the fiercely independent daughter of a missing adventurer, must push herself beyond her limits when she discovers the island where her father, Lord Richard Croft (Dominic West) disappeared.

fields.title: Dunkirk
fields.synopsis: Allied soldiers from Belgium, the British Commonwealth and Empire, and France are surrounded by the German Army and evacuated during a fierce battle in World War II.

fields.title: The Big Sick
fields.synopsis: Pakistan-born comedian Kumail Nanjiani and grad student Emily Gardner fall in love but struggle as their cultures clash. When Emily contracts a mysterious illness, Kumail finds himself forced to face her feisty parents, his family's expectations, and his true feelings.

fields.title: Your Name
fields.synopsis: Two strangers find themselves linked in a bizarre way. When a connection forms, will distance be the only thing to keep them apart?

fields.title: Room
fields.synopsis: Held captive for 7 years in an enclosed space, a woman and her young son finally gain their freedom, allowing the boy to experience the outside world for the first time.

fields.title: It Follows
fields.synopsis: A young woman is followed by an unknown supernatural force after a sexual encounter.

fields.title: Beautiful Boy
fields.synopsis: Based on the best-selling pair of memoirs from father and son David and Nic Sheff, Beautiful Boy chronicles the heartbreaking and inspiring experience of survival, relapse and recovery in a family coping with addiction over many years.

fields.title: The Lives of Others
fields.synopsis: In 1984 East Berlin, an agent of the secret police, conducting surveillance on a writer and his lover, finds himself becoming increasingly absorbed by their lives.
